comment: Create root directories.
Initial commit.
A bunch of bug fixes Added the --warning_level={QUIET|DEFAULT|VERBOSE} flag, to match the webservice API
Turn the symbol check off unless --warnings_level == VERBOSE
Remove timestamps from the javadoc, because they screw up the diffs. Also, better error messages.
Fix synthesis of vars in DEFAULT mode. Better variable inlining Better function inlining Assorted bug fixes
Fixes for issues 14 and 16.
- Fix issue #19 - attach jsdoc comments without annotations to nodes
Adding missing --check_types option. Hello type checker!
Better number printing. Add flags for fine-grained warning controls. Better type-declaration finding. Added some missing externs. Marked externs that don't have side effects.

Fix if-folding compiler crash (issue 43) Fix property-collapsing compiler crash (issue 34) Fix labeled VAR compiler crash (issue 41) Make [paramName] syntax denote optionality (issue #26) Better function inlining.
Never rename a variable named "$super", because the Prototype library uses this to do magic.
Don't warn about duplicate variable declarations unless warning_level is set to VERBOSE.
Better support for jsdoc toolkit annotations.

Add a mechanism for inlining local vars, and turn it on by default. Warnings for "ambiguous" function definitions. Refactoring and renaming of some method names. Use "=" optionality annotation in externs.
Add --define flag to the API. Remove the warning for ambiguous function definitions: it's not yet fully baked. Fix a bug in data-flow based variable inlining.
Add a debugging option for variable renaming. Bug fixes for direct calls on the arguments array.
Warn about all with statements, unless there's an explicit /** @suppress {with} */ tag
Fix a type-checking bug in instanceof.
Add buttloads of tests.
Add support for other charset types.
Better dead assignment elimination.
Add a pass for collecting symbols exported like window['x'] = ...
Add a --debug flag for easier debugging.
Add warnings for functions that are ambiguously defined on different browsers.
Fix for issue #75.
Rollback the new ambiguous function def warning, because it still has false positives.
Change the internal representation of constant variables.
Nicer descriptions for the flags api.
Add rictic's "ant fuzz-test" command
Minor code removal improvement "({}).prop = 3;" has no side effects.
Add a .classpath and .project file, for eclipse users.
Add svn:ignore for eclipse files, per Issue 79

Pre-compiling the protocol buffers to bytecode is lame. Instead, put the protocol buffer source code under src/, and the generated Java code into gen/ (so that you don't need to install the protocol compiler to compile the code).
Add build/ to svn:ignore
Update the .classpath file for new gen/ directory.
Add boatloads of tests.
Remove reference to base.X, which the guava team does not plan on open-sourcing
Add more unit tests for type checking.
Make the interfaces API a bit less specific.
inline a method from common libraries.
Fix up the inheritance hierarchy so that "Foo implements Bar" implies that Bar.prototype is the implicit prototype of Foo.prototoype.
Fixes a bug in AmbugateProperties in the presence of interfaces.
Make sure that the SourceMap (for debugging) is valid JSON by escaping strings correctly.
Turn on side-effect-based optimizations in advanced mode.
Fix an edge case in goog.provide handling.
Flesh out the chrome extensions api some more.
Adds the ability to use Closure Compiler in Ant. Can also be used in other systems like Gradle, Buildr and Maven. It's not feature complete, but it's a start.
Add a jquery externs file contributed by matias.
Use non-generic data structures in a bunch of places. (More for readability reasons than anything else)
Use ImmutableMap.Builder instead of ImmutableMapBuilder.
Corrections to the jquery externs file. Contributed by Peter Burns.
Silence all warnings in QUIET mode.
Better type checking for switch/case conditions.
updated .classpath to include ant_deploy.jar
Make sure that InlineVariables can inline variables that are never defined.
Allow the COMMA operator to be used to make a call to eval indirect.
Print indirect calls to eval correctly (issue 81)
Add an extern file for the w3c geolocation api.
Add some new externs files: webkit notifications, web storage, and file access.
Fix a null pointer exception in TypedScopeCreator
Split the junit jar into its component pieces: the hamcrest code, the junit code under org.* packages, and the junit code under the junit.* packages.
Don't do local type inference on local vars that are assigned in inner scopes, because it's pretty close to impossible to do it right.
Move the devirtualizer later in the optimization process. We're not really sure why this improves things (yet).
Make CompilerRunner package-private. There's no good reason for it to be public. And right now, users of the Java API are confused about whether they should use Compiler or CompilerRunner.
Google Maps JS API V3 Externs file. Contributed by Chad Kiilingsworth in Issue 94.
Make the FlagsUsageException protected.
fix up some more inference-on-inner-functions edge cases.
Type-checking fix when the prototype is assigned directly. Fixes issue 59.
Rewrite ProcessClosurePrimitives to have a distinct indexing and mutation step.
Fix a bunch of passes to preserve more type information.
Fix a bug in type inference when there are more than two inner functions in a local scope.
Update the Google Maps API V3 for api changes (fixes Issue 105). Contributed by Chad Killingsworth
Fix some bad type information in the default externs, and do a bit of tightening. Fixes issue 104.
Fix an edge case in how Array.prototype.join is collapsed. Fixes issue 106.
Add HTML5 MessagePort.
Speed up parsing a bit by refactoring how we pull jsdoc comments into the AST.
delete some dead code
Fix a null pointer exception in FunctionType.
Add an externs entry for Webkit's document.getCSSCanvasContext()
updated .classpath to reflect changes to lib/
don't run RemoveUnusedVars to a fixed point, because the PhaseOptimizer does that already.
push a few more externs into contrib/externs.
Allow @typedefs to never be assigned. (Nick Santos)
Fix chrome.tabs.sendRequest extern in javascript/chrome_externs.js. (Matias)
Runtime type check. (Nada and Andrew)
Fix getGreatestSubtype for UnionTypes by always returning the meet of the two types. (Andrew)
Fixes a bug in getGreatestSubtype (Andrew)
Make the CFA recognize possible ON_EX edges for instanceof operations. Fixes issue 113. (Alan)
Fix a bug in expression decomposition (Alan)
Merge NodeTypeNormalizer and CodingConventionAnnotator into a single pass. (Nick)
"var arguments" never shadows the built-in arguments array. Fixes issue 115.
emit the right error message when goog is required. (Nick)
Rename CompilerRunner -> CommandLineRunner. I'll also do this for JSCompilerRunner, but it will be a much bigger change. (Nick)
Changed CommandLineRunner to public, as I believe that was the intention according to http://groups.google.com/group/closure-compiler-discuss/browse_thread/thread/1e4e73765b1fd56f
Made the constructors for CommandLineRunner public again so it can be subclassed.
changed access level of constructors of CommandLineRunner to protected
Add docs for CommandLineRunner.
Updates google maps api v3 extern. Contributed by Chad Killingsworth.

Fix DisambiguateProperties whenever an inferface was unioned with a constructor. The problem is that processProperty would recurse twice--once to get the alternates of the union and once to get the interface implementations--and the related type would not get passed up the recursion stack. (Nick)

Change EventTarget to be an interface rather than a concrete class. Implement required methods on classes that derive from EventTarget. I didn't want to convert derived classes to be interfaces in this CL, but many of them should be change (nassar)
rolling back the EventTarget changes for a little bit
switch over to args4j (Nick) Fixes issue 11.
removed an unused import and fixed up overview javadoc
combine junit jars
update licensing info (Nick)
Add a pass type that just reports an error (Brad)
Run cross module code motion before and after devirtualization. (Alan)
Adds an 'originalPath' property to SourceFile.
Cache expensive hashcode calculations. (John)
Cache expensive hashcode calculations. (John)

Group Variable Declarations in Scope. Merges all variable declarations in a scope into the first var statement in that scope.
set proper mime-types for some html files.

Don't use NAME for label names, introduce LABEL_NAME. This improves the correctness of the compiler as many passes don't distinguish between label names and variable names appropriately. (John) R=robert DELTA=57  (29 added, 12 deleted, 16 changed)

In a world where the compiler figures out dependency info and auto-excludes files that aren't required, it's not scalable to parse every file. So switch to a source-based dependency analyzer. (Nick) R=andrew,andrew,robert DELTA=226  (146 added, 8 deleted, 72 changed)

Fix ExtractPrototypeMembers so that it uses a fixed variable names, so that it doesn't break normalization. As it turns out, JSTestC uses anonymous function naming. those anonymous function names are so long that it starts to blow out the browser's JsVM. They need prototype extraction to make the names shorter. (maybe this anonymous function "naming" is part of the cause of gmail's development woes? we should follow up to see how they're using it.)

Attach types to literals at scope-creation time instead of at inference time. Scope-creation already attaches types to function literals at scope-creation type, so this makes the other literals more consistent with function literals.

fix a weird integration issue. some processes run the provide/require processor after scope creation.  That means that TypedScopeCreator can't assign types to the new namespaces.  Normal closure compiler is moving towards a model where TypedScopeCreator declares namespaces in the global scope. It's not clear how we should resolve this inconsistency, but for now this shim will make things better.
Support author scrubbing for HTML-format comments. Also refactors author scrubber to be a comment-oriented scrubber rather than a line-oriented scrubber, so only comments are processed.

If a property is defined on a global name, but in a local scope, declare that property in the global scope. this goes most of the way towards fixing issue 66.
Cut variable coalescing runtime by about 40%. If we know that variables x and y intersect, then we don't have to look at them again.
If a name occurs also as a direct left child of an assignment expression, FlowSensitiveInlineVariables may still inline the variable. For example, x = x + 1.

Add half-assed support for late-resolved typedefs of union types. The fundamental issue is that NamedType is a proxy wrapper around ObjectTypes, but has always been used for non-object types (like typedef'd unions. I eventually want to move towards the using UnresolvedTypes for type resolution. Under that system, the proxy wrapper gets thrown away. UnresolveTypes would also solve this issue. But that system breaks a whole bunch of assumptions about hash codes and referential transparency, so we're not ready for it yet.

Clean up type discovery by refactoring to the following algorithm. 1) When we see a function literal, create the authoritative type for it. 2) When we see an object literal, create the authoritative type for it. 3) When we declare a symbol, check to see if it's assigned to an object or function literal, and use that type if it make sense to do so. Otherwise, fall back on the JSDoc info. This should make it a lot easier to give accurate types to object literal properties. Fix a nasty bug in collapseproperties. The problem is that the declaration-updater conflates "can i always collapse this name?" with "can i sometimes collapse children of this name?" There are a few rare cases where they are not equivalent, like if you have /** @constructor */ a.b.c = function() {}; where a is collapsed and a.b.c is collapsed (because constructors are always collapsed), but a.b is not. Proposal: change how we represent property sets on objects. I went down this rabbit-hole to experiment with a few different things: - Separating property bookkeeping from type relation bookkeeping. - Use the same property-store for "new Foo()" and "Foo.prototype". I don't think that maintaining separate property maps for these two types actually buys us anything, and it's inconsistent with how they're used in practice. - Use the same property-store for "Foo.<Bar>" and "Foo.<Baz>" I actually like how this ended up--it's a lot easier to see how properties are inherited. But I'm curious what others think.

Per-scope change detection validation in the unit tests is broken (the older all or nothing validation works correctly). Several issues: * There was a logic mismatch with regard to which Nodes should be checked and SCRIPT nodes were being ignored. * The validation was only run if the PhaseOptimizer set but CompilerTestCase does use PhaseOptimizer by default (some all but a few don't) * The validation was comparing the state before the setup passes ran (es6 transpilation, normalization, etc) so a unit test might pass even if it didn't mark a pass as changed. * The validate logic, in unit tests, was not checking scopes not marked as changed but only  validated that marked nodes had been changed (the latter is less likely to be  incorrect). * The validation logic was ignoring Node annotations when comparing node for changes which causes some false negative results.
